        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 5:47PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 546 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a band extending from near Butner to near Mebane to 7 miles
southeast of Graham to 7 miles northeast of Siler City to Goldston.
Movement was northwest at 20 mph. This band could produce tornadoes.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph, heavy rainfall.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Durham, Burlington, Graham, Roxboro, Hillsborough, Siler City,
Mebane, Butner, Goldston, and McLeansville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Continued heavy rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may
lead to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through
flooded roadways.

Doppler radar has indicated areas of weak rotation with this storm.
If the storm intensifies and rotation strengthens, a warning may
need to be issued.</instruction>
